cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper presents a toolkit for analyzing individual neurons in neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential applications of the toolkit in controlling data biases, which suggests a possible connection to natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential use of the toolkit for better architectural choices, which could be related to neural engineering (cs.NE).
